1. Boson contribution (complex scalar, 2 real d.o.f.):  
$$
\mathcal{E}_{\rm boson}
=2\cdot\frac12\int\frac{d^3k}{(2\pi)^3}\sqrt{k^2+m^2}
=\int\frac{d^3k}{(2\pi)^3}\sqrt{k^2+m^2}\,. 
$$

2. Fermion contribution (Majorana, 2 states):  
$$
\mathcal{E}_{\rm fermion}
=-2\cdot\frac12\int\frac{d^3k}{(2\pi)^3}\sqrt{k^2+m^2}
=-\int\frac{d^3k}{(2\pi)^3}\sqrt{k^2+m^2}\,. 
$$

3. Total vacuum energy density:  
$$
\mathcal{E}_{\rm vac}
=\mathcal{E}_{\rm boson}+\mathcal{E}_{\rm fermion}
=\int\frac{d^3k}{(2\pi)^3}\sqrt{k^2+m^2}
-\int\frac{d^3k}{(2\pi)^3}\sqrt{k^2+m^2}
=0\,. 
$$
